SUGAR IS GOLDEN was under a tight rein, content to watch the contesting duo three wide outside down the backside, inched closer at the quarter pole, loomed outside in the four path at the top of the stretch but could not match strides with the winner at the furlong pole and settled on a clear second at the wire. SOMEONE ELSE pressed the pace outside down the backstretch and through the turn, was scrubbed on between horses vying for the lead in upper stretch, could not go on with the top pair down the lane and stubbornly resurged late to save third money. OHEAVENS travelled in mid-pack between foes in the two path down the backside, crept closer on the fence behind the leaders running around the bend, was in for a share of the prize on the rail straightening out for the drive but was outfinished late for the show award. LIPLOCK tracked four deep on the outside down the backstretch, came under a ride making little headway four wide outside horses through the turn, was in range in the five path turning for home but could not find more late and stalled at the furlong marker. WICKED MIAH settled in midfield in the three path between runners in the early going, was roused with rivals on each side in midturn but made little impact and could not be a presence running through the stretch. STORMY SUZIE was unhurried trailing down the back straight, caught up to the field passing a rival outside with five sixteenths to go, swung out to the five path for the drive but could not get involved down the lane. PACENZA had a good position tucked in on the rail just behind the engaging leaders down the backside, was checked mildly on the fence three furlongs from home, shuffled back trailing by the midpoint on the turn and was not a factor in the drive to the wire.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPRING MOUNTAIN rated kindly all alone in the third flight down the backstretch, was smartly picking up runners three wide around the final turn, loomed boldly in the four path straightening out for home and determinedly wore down the leader through the stretch to get up just before the wire. NEWPORT AGENT stalked near the rear down the backside, began to lengthen stride inside at the half, waited briefly behind a tiring runner midway around the final bend, slipped up the fence at the quarter pole and finished gamely to just hold for third money in a tight photo. HELL BENT was nestled on the rail behind the trio of leaders down the backside, was coaxed for more gaining inside throughout the far turn, appeared to have stalled a touch in upper stretch then gamely burst between runners finding another gear at the sixteenth pole and just missed with the late surge losing the show photo. DESOLATOR settled nicely all alone in midfield down the backstretch, commenced a rally three wide with three eighths to run, angled outside to be beside the eventual winner turning for home but was outkicked by others in the final furlong. SUNRISE DRIVE stumbled on the break, trailed the field down the backside, offered a mild rally three wide midpoint on the final turn, angled out to the six path for the stretch drive and willingly finished up running to the wire. SEVEN IS A BREEZE hopped then bobbled at the start, stalked close to the rear having one beat down the backstretch, swung out with momentum seven wide for the drive but could not get involved running to the wire. NATIVE PRINCE took this field into the first turn, set the pace up front on the rail while hounded outside down the back straight, maintained a slim advantage on the fence at the quarter pole, could not quicken with others at the top of the lane and was engulfed by rivals outside in mid-stretch. STRONG ENDING pressed the issue on the outside into the first turn, continued to badger the frontrunner between rivals down the backstretch, was asked for more but had little to give dueling up front three furlongs from home and backed away through the field midway on the final turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WOODBINE RACE 10 6F All Weather Track CR: 83. Maiden Optional Claiming Purse 65900. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD ONTARIO SIRED MAIDENS OR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD MAIDEN CLAIMING PRICE $40,000. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHAIRMAN RAINBOW dueled briefly then took the advantage from outside two to three deep forcing the pace, moved clear by the three-eighths, was kept to the task and held sway. ONE TRUE GENTLEMAN settled in behind stalking the leading pair, went two wide between foes on the turn, kept on late to close the gap but couldn't reach the winner. MIDNIGHT TEMPESTA contended from inside the eventual winner, lost ground on that one into the turn, switched out and drifted five wide turning for home, kept on in the lane but needed more. FABLED PRINCE settled mid-division off the rail, fanned seven to eight wide into upper stretch, finished up strongly to gain late. ROAD TO VERSAILLES was bumped sideways at the start, raced at the back off the inside, fanned four wide into upper stretch then shifted in once in mid-stretch for room and finished up willingly. ASK IN MY NAME bumped the outer rival at the start, settled off the pace racing between foes on the turn three to four deep, moved out in upper stretch, kicked on well but too late. MODEL S moved forward between foes into the turn in range of the leaders three to four wide, lacked the needed late kick. COHERENCE stalked from a forward position, moved out from four to six wide on the turn, weakened in the stretch. SO CALLED VACATION broke outwardly, was caught five wide toward the rear on the turn, moved out further in upper stretch, failed to menace. DEMBA failed to menace while racing off the inside four to five deep on the turn. JUST FOR MADDIE broke a half-step slowly, moved forward inside under mild coaxing, tracked along the rail about mid-pack into the turn, steadied past the three-eighths, failed to rally thereafter. HYGGE was forced out a bit and off slowly at the start, lacked any early speed despite encouragement, trailed inside into the turn. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF JUST FOR MADDIE AGAINST ONE TRUE GENTLEMAN ALLEGING INTERFERENCE, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
